Trifolium campestre

   [10527.jpg]
   Authority Schreber
   Family Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Fabales:Leguminosae
   Synonyms Trifolium procumbens L.
   Common names hop clover, hop trefoil, large hop clover, trefle couche',
   feldklee, told klee, trifoglio giallo, trifoglio olandese, trebol del
   campo, trevo namorado, erva do amor, trebol amarillo
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 10527

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION
   A clover with small round heads of yellow flowers that turn brown upon
   ripening of the seed.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Herb.
   COMMON NAMES
   Large hop clover.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Heath M 1985 pp 144 [DRA, FER, TEXT, USE]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 160 [USE]
   Duke J 1981 pp 320 [TEMP, RAIN, PH]

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
